On National Agriculture Day, President Donald Trump acknowledges the hard work and contributions of American farmers. He highlights the importance of the agricultural sector in the country's economy, noting that every $1 of agricultural and food exports creates another $1.27 in business activity. The value of agriculture exports exceeds $100 billion and supports thousands of jobs. The President emphasizes the innovation and technological advancements in agriculture, such as biotechnology and automated vehicles. He also mentions the investments being made in rural infrastructure, including broadband access and power supply. President Trump mentions the Tax Cuts and Jobs Act, which provides relief to farmers by allowing them to expense 100 percent of their capital investments and exempts the majority of family farms from the death tax. He proclaims March 20, 2018, as National Agriculture Day and encourages Americans to recognize the importance of agriculture in their daily lives and express appreciation for those working in the agriculture sector.